    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="705"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d705">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/610</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-22">April 22,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Ambassador<note n="14" xml:id="d705fn14">Viscount Halifax.</note>
                    called to see me this morning at his request.</p>
                <p>The Ambassador again raised the question of the recognition by the United States
                    of the independence of Syria. I replied that, in view <pb facs="0603" n="591"
                        xml:id="pg_591"/> of the events in France in the past few days, I felt that
                    the time would soon come when this Government would wish to give further
                    consideration to this question. I took occasion to communicate to the Ambassador
                    the substance of Mr. Engert’s telegram of this morning<note n="15"
                        xml:id="d705fn15">Presumably telegram No. 142 of April 21, <hi rend="italic"
                            >supra</hi>.</note> indicating the complete discord between the Free
                    French representative in Syria and the British representative, General Spears.
                    …</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
